   <head>Ad Lectorem.</head>
   <p>PVerum (vt inquit Lilius apud Anglos Grāmaticus non ig<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>nobilis) nil nisi pura decent. In Terentio est pura oratio: materia vrò vt plurimù impura: nec mirum. Quid enim aliud â misello e<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap>h<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap>ico, verum Deum verae pu<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="2 letters">
         <desc>••</desc>
      </gap>tat<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap>s tontem igno<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>ra<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap>te, exp<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap>ctare possis? Operaepr<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap>tium itaque fecit Schonaeus vir doctissimus, qui in grati<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap>m Christianae pueritiae materias castiores pura Terentij phrasi vestiuerit, vt pueritia vnà cum orationis elegan<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap>i<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap>, morum quoque sanctitatem &amp; probita<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>tem imbiberet▪ Pauc<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap> autem delibauimu<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap>, quia in hoc genere p<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap>uca suffi<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="2 letters">
         <desc>••</desc>
      </gap>re videantur. Apocrypha vero <gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap>elex<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap>mus, nō quia sanctio<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap>a aut veriora, sed quia lusibus aptiora indicamus: im<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>primis Tobijam &amp; Iuditham, quorum vtrumque doctus qui<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>dam Theologus sacrum potius poema, quam historiam appel<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>landum a<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap>b<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap>tratur: Notum est praeterea &amp; vulgari sermone tritum prouerbiū: Non est bonum cum sanctis ludere. Quid autem scripturis canon<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap>cis diuinitus inspiratis augustius &amp; sanctius inter homines inuen<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap>ri potest? His itaque addere, detrahere, omittere, sermones &amp; personas affingere, &amp; hu<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>iusmodi quae poetica licentia postulat, nonnullis quos teme<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>re offensos nolumus, religio est. N<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap>m quae in his libris vel fal<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>sa vel dura, vel impura videri possunt, <gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap>a p<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap>orum praecepto<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>rum prudentiae relinquo, Vale Lect<gap reason="illegible" resp="#apex" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap>r amice, &amp; ista vel omit<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>te vel fruere bono tuo.</p>
